item.title: Ruxcon 11 â€” Pwnable 2
item.description: This was the second pwnable challenge at Ruxcon 11. Players would SSH into a server running 64 bit Ubuntu and the SSH user’s home directory contained two files: level2 and tokenfile. file and cat quickly revealed that level2 is a x86-64 ELF executable that hasn’t been stripped. tokenfile is a text file but we can’t read it. Presumably then the aim of the challenge is to read that file!
